%div#projects.features
  %div.wrapper
    .row
      %br/
      %h1.text-center.title PROJECTS
      %br/

      .row
      .col-xs-12
        .thumbnail
          =image_tag("dissertation.png", alt: "Project 3", class: "img-responsive logo")
        .caption
          %b Let's Eat Together
          is my dissertation project of MSc(Eng) Advanced Software Engineeering degree from University of Sheffield. This is a cross-platform application built using
          = link_to 'https://ionicframework.com/', target: :_blank do
            Ionic 2 framework
          and Node.js as the backend server that utilises SQLite database and RESTful API. It is a meal- event creation mobile application where people can host meal events at local eatery and others may join these events. People can also get recommended events
          whenever they "star" users they like. 
          %p
          %p
            %b *Demo: 
            = link_to 'https://lets-eat-together-app.herokuapp.com/', target: :_blank do
              https://lets-eat-together-app.herokuapp.com/
            %br/
            %b Project Repository on Github: 
            = link_to 'https://github.com/Christian-007/eatTogether', target: :_blank do
              https://github.com/Christian-007/eatTogether
          %p.info *Please open this demo from a mobile phone or use the mobile view feature on Google Chrome to get the suitable screen size as its layout is based on mobile phones. Some features (such as Upload picture) may not work since it requires FileStorage API of targeted mobile platform.

        .caption-tag
          %b Tags:
          %span.skills Ionic 2
          %span.skills Angular 2 (TypeScript)
          %span.skills SQLite
          %span.skills Node.js
          %span.skills RESTful API

      .col-sm-6.col-xs-12
        .thumbnail
          =image_tag("gallerysite.png", alt: "Project 1", class: "img-responsive logo")
        .caption
          %b Gallery Viewer
          is an e-commerce website dedicated for selling pictures/photos of scenery. It is a solo
          project and created to fill my spare time. This website has an admin feature where the user 
          can modify several pages of the website.
          %p
          %p
            %b Project Repository on Github: 
            = link_to 'https://github.com/Christian-007/gallery-website', target: :_blank do
              https://github.com/Christian-007/gallery-website
        .caption-tag
          %b Tags:
          %span.skills HTML
          %span.skills CSS3
          %span.skills Bootstrap
          %span.skills jQuery
          %span.skills PHP
          %span.skills AJAX
          %span.skills MySQL
          %span.skills Angular.js
          %span.skills Grunt.js

      .col-sm-6.col-xs-12
        .thumbnail
          =image_tag("projectacq.png", alt: "Project 2", class: "img-responsive logo")
        .caption
          %b Project Acquisition Application
          is a Ruby on Rails web application that can handle project submission from clients to module leaders registered in University of Sheffield. This is a part of Training Project of epiGenesys, 
          a student-led software development organisation in Sheffield (
          %a{:href => 'https://www.epigenesys.org.uk/', target: :_blank} epiGenesys website
          )
        .caption-tag
          %b Tags:
          %span.skills Ruby On Rails
          %span.skills Bootstrap
          %span.skills SASS
          %span.skills jQuery
          %span.skills AJAX
          %span.skills Postgresql

    .row
      .col-xs-12
        / %a{:href => "", 'data-toggle' => "modal", 'data-target' => "#modalPicture", class: "ajax-modal"}
        / = link_to home_path(id: 1), class: 'ajax-modal', 'data-toggle': 'ajax-modal' do
        .thumbnail
          =image_tag("liftlog_compressed.png", alt: "Project 3", class: "img-responsive logo")
        .caption
          %b LiftLog
          is a pair project of the module Software Development for Mobile Devices (COM6510) from University of Sheffield. This is an iOS application
          focusing on a workout tracking. It can create daily workout routines,  add exercises to the routines, and store workout sets and repetitions for each exercise. On top of that, the users can get recent workout news/articles, which are retained from RSS of  a certain body building website. This app also implements a map that can show nearby gyms based on current user's location.
          %p
          %p
            %b Project Repository on Github: 
            = link_to 'https://github.com/Christian-007/iOSProject', target: :_blank do
              https://github.com/Christian-007/iOSProject
        .caption-tag
          %b Tags:
          %span.skills Objective-C
          %span.skills Core Data
          %span.skills XML Parsing
          %span.skills Segue Storyboard
          %span.skills MapKit

    .row
      .col-xs-12
        .thumbnail
          =image_tag("tardis.png", alt: "TaRDIS", class: "img-responsive logo")
        .caption
          %b Time and Resourcing Data Information System (TaRDIS)
          is a Ruby on Rails web application that can assist Clinical Trials Research Unit (CTRU) of University of
          Sheffield in Data Management process. It will manage the Data Management process, such as managing Studies, Tasks, and the time spent on each task by staff efficiently. These are handled by using sort of a Gantt chart
          application on the web with added features, such as add people to tasks and time management report. The Gantt
          chart itself is created manually (not using any Gantt Chart API) by utilising some of Bootstrap features to generate columns, combined with Ruby on Rails controllers and Active Record. This project is still under development and a part of Genesys 2 module of University of Sheffield.
        .caption-tag
          %b Tags:
          %span.skills Ruby On Rails
          %span.skills Bootstrap
          %span.skills SASS
          %span.skills jQuery
          %span.skills AJAX
          %span.skills Postgresql

